    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-12-23T13:44:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-12-23T13:44:00-05:00" n="362"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d362">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">882.124A/19: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Liberia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wharton</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Monrovia</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-12-23T18:00:00-00:44"
                            >December 23, 1929—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received December 24—11:48 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Convinced Liberia will not commit itself definitely at this time to the $15,000
                    in article No. 3 as submitted and reported in my 68, December 3, 9 p.m. I have
                    submitted alternate proposal article 3 as quoted in the Department’s 50,
                    November 23, 6 p.m.</p>
                <p>Barclay states that if following form of article 3 meets with the approval of the
                    Department, instruction may be issued sanitary engineer to proceed to Monrovia.
                    Second sentence of article No. 3 to read as follows: “An additional $3,000 shall
                    be provided should the chief medical adviser satisfy the Liberian Government
                    that the sum of $12,000 is insufficient for these purposes.” In the [last?]
                    sentence change “thereunder” to “there out.”</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wharton</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
